## MANDATORY RULES - DO NOT DEVIATE

### Architecture
- Use the `app/` directory (App Router). NEVER use `pages/`.
- Server Components are the DEFAULT. Only add `'use client'` when required.
- Do NOT use `getServerSideProps`, `getStaticProps`, or `getInitialProps`.

### File naming
- Every route becomes `app/<path>/page.tsx`
- Shared layout: `app/layout.tsx`
- 404 page: `app/not-found.tsx`
- Error boundary: `app/error.tsx`
- Loading skeleton: `app/loading.tsx`

### Metadata
- Static metadata: `export const metadata: Metadata = { title: '...', description: '...' }`
- Dynamic metadata: `export async function generateMetadata({ params }): Promise<Metadata> {}`
- NEVER use react-helmet in Next.js. Remove all Helmet imports and components.

### Data fetching
- If a component fetched data in useEffect or useQuery AND the data is NOT user-specific:
  -> Make the component async, remove the hook, fetch() directly at the top level
  -> Return the data as props to any interactive child components
- If data IS user-specific (auth-gated): keep client-side data fetching
- `fetch()` in Server Components is automatically cached by Next.js

### Client Component rules
- A component needs `'use client'` ONLY if it uses:
  useState, useReducer, useEffect, useCallback, useRef, useMemo,
  browser APIs (window/document/localStorage),
  or JSX event handlers (onClick, onChange, onSubmit)
- Add `'use client'` as the FIRST line of the file when required

### Routing
- React Router's `<Link to="/path">` -> `import Link from 'next/link'; <Link href="/path">`
- `useNavigate()` -> `import { useRouter } from 'next/navigation'; const router = useRouter()`
- `useParams()` -> access via `props.params` in Server Components
- Dynamic routes: `/product/:id` -> `app/product/[id]/page.tsx`

### Images
- `<img src="...">` -> `import Image from 'next/image'; <Image src="..." width={} height={} alt="..." />`
- Always provide width and height to prevent CLS

### Environment variables
- `process.env.REACT_APP_*` -> `process.env.NEXT_PUBLIC_*` (for client-exposed vars)
- Server-only vars: just `process.env.MY_VAR` (no prefix needed in Server Components)

### package.json
- REMOVE: react-router-dom, react-helmet, react-helmet-async, react-scripts
- ADD: next@14, (keep react and react-dom)
- UPDATE scripts: `"dev": "next dev"`, `"build": "next build"`, `"start": "next start"`

